From: Sarveshwar Bandi <sarveshwar.bandi@emulex.com>
Date: Fri, 23 Aug 2013 14:59:33 +0530
Subject: be2net: Check for POST state in suspend-resume sequence
Patch-mainline: v3.11
Git-commit: dd5746bf6b48bb837e9f5af14b9b241fc4fdc1ef
References: bnc#835189

In suspend-resume sequence, the OS could attempt to initialize the controller
before it is ready, check for POST state before going ahead.

Signed-off-by: Sarveshwar Bandi <sarveshwar.bandi@emulex.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
@@ -4220,6 +4220,10 @@ static int be_resume(struct pci_dev *pde
 	pci_set_power_state(pdev, 0);
 	pci_restore_state(pdev);
 
+	status = be_fw_wait_ready(adapter);
+	if (status)
+		return status;
+
 	/* tell fw we're ready to fire cmds */
 	status = be_cmd_fw_init(adapter);
 	if (status)
